<subSubSection id="AC8E4B8151A218CFFF0EFF40EE2C1DCD" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51A218CFFF0EFF40EE2C1DCD" blockId="153.[151,1437,223,394]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851A218CFFF0EFF40EE3C1CBE" bold="true" box="[151,260,223,249]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Remarks</emphasis>
. Recorded from 
<collectingRegion id="2650D6E851A218CFFE5CFF40ED2F1CBE" box="[453,535,223,249]" country="Philippines" name="Manila" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Manila</collectingRegion>
, the species was described as dorsally pale, with the elytral apex black, and the basal abdominal segments brown. Nothing sufficiently distinctive about this colour pattern, nor the locality data, would permit an attempt to associate males. 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51A218CFFD1EFEB8EC6C1D06" author="McDermott" box="[647,852,295,321]" firstAuthor="McDermott" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref119380" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae. In: Steel, W. O. (Ed.), Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 9. Editio Secunda. W. Junk, S'Gravenhage, pp. 1 - 149." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott (1966</bibRefCitation>
; 99) incorrectly attributed a reference to this species to 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51A218CFFF2AFED4EE7D1D22" author="Olliff" box="[179,325,331,357]" firstAuthor="Olliff" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="643 - 653" refId="ref121121" refString="Olliff, A. S. (1890) New species of Lampyridae, including a notice of the Mt. Wilson Firefly. Proceedings of the Linnaean Society of New South Wales, 4 (2), 643 - 653 + 1297. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 15062" type="journal article" year="1890">Olliff (1890)</bibRefCitation>
. Olliff referred to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951A218CFFD97FED4EC2F1D22" authority="Gemm." authorityName="Gemminger. Not" authorityYear="1870" box="[526,791,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dejeani">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851A218CFFD97FED4ED841D22" box="[526,700,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Luciola dejeani</emphasis>
Gemm.
</taxonomicName>
which he equated to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951A218CFFB9BFED3EBCA1D22" authority="Boisduval" authorityName="Boisduval" box="[1026,1266,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851A218CFFB9BFED3EB401D22" box="[1026,1144,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">L. apicalis</emphasis>
Boisduval
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951A218CFFABEFED3EE281DCD" authority="(Eschsch.)" authorityName="Eschsch." baseAuthorityName="Eschscholtz" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851A218CFFABEFED3EAA51D22" box="[1319,1437,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">L. apicalis</emphasis>
(Eschsch.)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
